                    <row>
                        <cell>6/1/43</cell>
                        <cell>In copy of informal talk, Mr. Ruess says other names for Sian are
                            Chang-an and Siking (123 Ruess, Waldo/123).</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>11/6/42</cell>
                        <cell>Drumright arrived Sian. Tel. says regular office will not be
                            established. An officer of the Embassy will be detailed to Sian and will
                            be addressed "Secretary of Embassy on detail at Sian, China". All
                            telegrams to and from Dept. will be through the Embassy. The officer
                            will be commissioned at Kunming in order that he may perform some
                            consular functions for American citizens. Under supervision of Embassy,
                            except re consular functions which will be under supervision of Congen.
                            at Kunming.</cell>
                    </row>
